
Overview of verb slide

The verb slide has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (18) skid, slip, slue, slew, slide -- (move obliquely or sideways, usually in an uncontrolled manner; "the wheels skidded against the sidewalk")
2. (14) slither, slide -- (to pass or move unobtrusively or smoothly; "They slid through the wicket in the big gate")
3. (3) slide -- (move smoothly along a surface; "He slid the money over to the other gambler")
